[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi again,<br>\nI try to write a driver which does:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create a platform device</li>\n<li>Register chrdev_region of MAX_CHRDEV devices</li>\n<li>On probe, afer reading some I/O, register a chrdev in the allocated region</li>\n</ul>\n<p>But I'm stuck on the step \"during probe, get access to the chrdev_region\"</p>\n<p>Actually I have this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_char_dev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">chrdev</span>::<span class=\"n\">Registration</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">MAX_BUSSES</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_pdev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">platform</span>::<span class=\"n\">Registration</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Bus</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">base</span>: <span class=\"nc\">IoMem</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mi\">252</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">type</span> <span class=\"nc\">BusData</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">device</span>::<span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Bus</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span>::<span class=\"n\">Driver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">probe</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"nc\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span>::<span class=\"n\">Device</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">_id_info</span>: <span class=\"nc\">core</span>::<span class=\"n\">option</span>::<span class=\"nb\">Option</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">IdInfo</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span>::<span class=\"n\">Data</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">res_mem</span>: <span class=\"nc\">IoMem</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mi\">252</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dev</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ioremap_resource</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">minor</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">res_mem</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">readl</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">REG_USER_ID</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// Here I want to access MyDriver._char_dev to register a device with the minor</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"c1\">// The C version of this driver use a static global \"major\" and cdev_init/cdev_add/device_create to achieve that, but there may be a better way to do that in rust</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span>::<span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">name</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">CStr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module</span>: <span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span> <span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">char_dev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">chrdev</span>::<span class=\"n\">Registration</span>::<span class=\"n\">new_pinned</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">map_err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">pr_err</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Failed to register char device: {:?}</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">e</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">pdev</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">platform</span>::<span class=\"n\">Registration</span>::<span class=\"n\">new_pinned</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">map_err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">pr_err</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s\">\"Failed to register platform: {:?}</span><span class=\"se\">\\n</span><span class=\"s\">\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">e</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">})</span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">MyDriver</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">_char_dev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">char_dev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">_pdev</span>: <span class=\"nc\">pdev</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 342080439,
        "sender_full_name": "Louis Chauvet",
        "timestamp": 1678891930
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I found a way to do that, but it's ugly I think, and maybe not safe:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">__MOD</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"nb\">Some</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"nb\">None</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">return</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ENODEV</span><span class=\"p\">),</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It allows me to register on existing chardevice, but I think it's not a good idea to do that (what happens if two probes happens in the same time ?  I don't know enough about the kernel to know if it is necessary for the probe function to be reentrant)<br>\nI may need something like a mutex to avoid those problem.</p>\n<p>For my tests it will be sufficient (I have only one device), but if you have a better solution I will be very happy to use it :</p>",
        "id": 342340481,
        "sender_full_name": "Louis Chauvet",
        "timestamp": 1678979061
